cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with formal verification techniques for business processes using logic-based approaches such as Action Languages and Model-Checking. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the modelling and execution of (business) processes or services using IT-systems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes an approach to reason on imperative data-aware process models using techniques such as Classical Planning. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is a possible category as the paper deals with incomplete log information and proposes an approach to exploit reachability to reason on data-aware process models. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the mapping between data-aware models and Action Languages, which are programming languages for reasoning about actions and change.
